        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Our primary aim is the CO(3-2) line with a complementary detection of the CO(4-3) in Band 3 as desireable.
Dust continuum is another benefit of the observation but not the principal goal.

line sensitivity was derived from the 0.2 L* estimate of Obreschkow et al (2011) for a z=3 MW progenitor, assumed to be typical for a resolution element of the lensed MW-analog galaxy. Typical magnification in an ALMA resolution element is assumed to be a factor ~10 (conservative estimate).

in 40 km/s bins, assuming a s/n=5 and peak flux of 1mJy, we ask for 2.7 hr per pointing to ensure several line detections per z=3 galaxy. 

Two of our targets are in a single pointing. We ask only for ALMA observations of those z=3 galaxies for which a spectroscopic confirmation of the photo-z exists, eliminating the need for a spectral scan of Band 3.





</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
